Create a Django project, and then create a simple URL shortener app using the Django framework. This app should include a template for users to submit a URL. This app should be capable of shortening the URL, displaying the newly shortened URL to the user, and counting the clicks on a URL. Create a admin page to view the clock count of a URL on Django admin. User 6 randomly generated characters to create the shortened URL. Additionally, it should have the functionality to redirect the shortened URL to the original URL. Ensure that all the necesaary files for running a Django application, such are manage.py, settings.py, urls.py and the wsgi file, are included. The app should use SQlite as its database.